ğŸ“Œ `alt` helps with accessibility & SEO

---

ğŸ§± Semantic Elements (Very Important)

Semantic tags give **meaning** to content.

| Tag         | Purpose             |
| ----------- | ------------------- |
| `<header>`  | Top section         |
| `<nav>`     | Navigation          |
| `<section>` | Content section     |
| `<article>` | Independent content |
| `<aside>`   | Sidebar             |
| `<footer>`  | Bottom section      |

ğŸ“Œ Used in **modern websites**

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§© HTML Block vs Inline Elements

Block Elements

* Take full width
* Start on new line
  Examples: `<div>`, `<p>`, `<h1>`

Inline Elements

* Take only required space
  Examples: `<span>`, `<a>`, `<img>`

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  HTML Attributes

Attributes provide **extra information**.

```html
<input type="text" placeholder="Enter name" required>
```

Common attributes:

* `id`
* `class`
* `style`
* `title`
* `placeholder`
* `required`

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âŒ Common Mistakes (Intermediate Level)

* Not using semantic tags
* Forgetting `alt` in images
* Poor indentation
* Overusing `<div>`

---

ğŸ’¡ Best Practices

* Use semantic HTML
* Keep code clean & readable
* Use proper labels in forms
* Always validate input

